   "text": "最大的咸水湖青海湖。青海湖被誉为“中国最美的湖泊”,是最受欢迎的旅游景点之一,也是摄影师和艺 术家的天堂。 青海山川壮丽,地大物博,石油和天然气储量丰富,省内许多城市的经济在石油和天然气工业带动下得 到了长足发展。青海尤以水资源丰富而闻名,是中国三大河流长江,黄河和澜沧江的发源地,在中国的水 生态中发挥着重要作用。",
   "reference": "Qinghai Lake is the largest saltwater lake. Known as \"China's most beautiful lake,\" it is one of the most popular tourist attractions and a paradise for photographers and artists. Qinghai boasts magnificent landscapes, vast territory, and abundant resources, with rich reserves of oil and natural gas. Driven by the oil and natural gas industries, the economies of many cities in the province have achieved considerable development. Qinghai is particularly renowned for its abundant water resources, serving as the source of China's three major rivers—the Yangtze, the Yellow, and the Lancang—and playing a vital role in the country's water ecology.",
