   "directions": "Translate the passage from Chinese into English.",
   "text": "汉语现在是世界上用作本族语人数最多的语言。汉语与西方语言的一个重要区别在于它是以方块字 (character)而不是以字母构成的。目前仍在使用的书写系统中，汉语是最古老的。在中国，来自不同地区的 人可能听不懂对方的方言，但由于汉字有统一的书写形式，他们交流起来几乎没有任何困难。汉语历史上 对团结中华民族发挥了重要作用。今天，随着中国经济的快速增长和全球影响力的增强，越来越多其他国 家的人也开始学习汉语。",
   "reference": "Chinese is now the language with the largest number of native speakers in the world. An important difference between Chinese and Western languages lies in that it is composed of characters rather than letters. Among the writing systems still in use, Chinese is the oldest. In China, people from different regions may not understand each other's dialects, but due to the unified written form of Chinese characters, they can communicate with almost no difficulty. Historically, the Chinese language has played a vital role in uniting the Chinese nation. Today, with China's rapid economic growth and increasing global influence, more and more people from other countries are beginning to learn Chinese.",
