   "directions": "Translate the passage from Chinese into English.",
   "text": "唐朝始于 618 年，终于 907 年，是中国历史上最灿烂的时期。经过近三百年的发展，唐代中国成为世界上 最繁荣的强国，其首都长安是当时世界上最大的都市。这一时期，经济发达、商业繁荣、社会秩序稳定，甚 至边境也对外开放。随着城市化和财富的增加，艺术和文学也繁荣起来。李白和杜甫是以作品简洁自然而著 称的诗人。他们的诗歌打动了学者和普通人的心。即使在今天，他们的许多诗歌仍广为儿童及成人阅读背诵。",
   "reference": "The Tang Dynasty, which began in 618 and ended in 907, was the most brilliant period in Chinese history. After nearly 300 years of development, Tang China became the most prosperous and powerful country in the world, with its capital Chang'an being the largest metropolis of the time. During this period, the economy was developed, commerce flourished, and social order was stable, with even the border areas being open to the outside world. As urbanization and wealth increased, art and literature also thrived. Li Bai and Du Fu were poets renowned for the simplicity and naturalness of their works. Their poems touched the hearts of both scholars and common people. Even today, many of their poems are still widely read and recited by children and adults alike.",
